This is an official Melius UI-only template for a customer success management command center.

Preserve existing data-melius-ui-id and data-melius-ui-role values unless the user explicitly asks to rename visual editor metadata.
Do not add data-melius-id, data-melius-form, data-melius-action, or data-melius-view in the template source by default.
Do not add src/melius.app-spec.json, src/melius.client.ts, or src/melius.actions.ts to the template source.
If the user asks for saving accounts, syncing CRM data, sending emails, alerts, authentication, billing, notifications, or other platform behavior, add the required Melius App Spec and data-melius-* bindings during the generated app editing flow, not as part of the UI-only template baseline.
Keep UI styling editable by the visual editor: prefer static className strings on real HTML elements inside the template UI kit.
Keep filters, tables, charts, forms, account rows, and action buttons visually complete, but treat them as presentational UI until Melius bindings are added later.
